```python
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    avg_stock_price = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=avg_stock_price)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average stock price of each company?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

```python
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', hue='symbol', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of stock prices over time for each company?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
